oard flipped, said no and of course ate everything I wrote (remind me to compose somewhere else next time). So I will try again. <br>
<br>
Everything from the &lt;script to the &lt;/script&gt; goes into the header on your page. This is the javascript that actually does the work.<br>
<br>
&lt;script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript"&gt;<br>
&lt;!-- hides script from non Javascript Browsers<br>
function goto(){<br>
	if (document.goto_selection.Link_Selecter.options[document.goto_selection.Link_Selecter.selectedIndex].value != "none") {<br>
		location = document.goto_selection.Link_Selecter.options[document.goto_selection.Link_Selecter.selectedIndex].value<br>
	}<br>
}<br>
//Ends Hiding--&gt;<br>
&lt;/script&gt;<br>
<br>
Everything from &lt;form to &lt;/form&gt; goes into the body where you want the select box to show up. You need to replace the URL# with the URL of the link you want and replace the NAME# with the Name of the link. To add more entries just copy &lt;option value="URL1"&gt;Name1&lt;/option&gt; and paste it right affter the others.<br>
<br>
&lt;form name="goto_selection"&gt;<br>
&lt;select name="Link_Selecter" size=1&gt;<br>
	&lt;option value="URL1"&gt;Name1&lt;/option&gt;<br>
	&lt;option value="URL2"&gt;Name2&lt;/option&gt;<br>
&lt;/select&gt;<br>
&lt;input type="button" value="Go" onclick="goto()"&gt;<br>
&lt;/form&gt;<br>
<br>
Let me know if this is not what you were referring to.<br>
<br>
Astryne the Lurker.<br>
